<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Nexus API/RPC Architecture Map</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #f7f7f9;
    --surface: #fff;
    --surface-2: #fafafb;
    --border: #e4e4e8;
    --border-strong: #c2c2c8;
    --text: #18181b;
    --text-muted: #6b7280;
    --text-faint: #9ca3af;
    --accent: #1466b8;
    --accent-bg: #e8f0fa;
    --supported: #15803d;
    --unavailable: #9ca3af;
    --other: #b45309;
    --todo: #dc2626;
    --t-cli: #2563eb;
    --t-rpc: #059669;
    --t-call: #047857;
    --t-expose: #0891b2;
    --t-http: #ea580c;
    --t-mcp: #7c3aed;
    --t-sdk: #db2777;
    --layer-transport: #fef3c7;
    --layer-cross: #ddd6fe;
    --layer-brick: #d1fae5;
    --layer-deployment: #fed7aa;
    --layer-nexus_fs: #dbeafe;
    --layer-rust_kernel: #fce7f3;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif; margin: 0; background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr; min-height: 100vh; }
  aside { position: sticky; top: 0; align-self: start; height: 100vh; overflow-y: auto; padding: 1.5rem 1rem 2rem; border-right: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--surface); }
  aside h2 { font-size: 0.7rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text-muted); margin: 1.2rem 0 0.4rem; }
  aside h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
  aside a { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 0.5rem; color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  aside a:hover { background: var(--accent-bg); color: var(--accent); }
  aside .count { color: var(--text-faint); font-size: 0.75rem; }
  aside .brand { font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.05rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; color: var(--text); }
  aside .brand-sub { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.78rem; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  main { padding: 2rem 2.5rem 4rem; max-width: 1180px; }
  h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
  .subtitle { color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0 0 1.5rem; max-width: 60ch; }
  .stats { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr); gap: 0.75rem; margin: 0 0 2rem; }
  .stat { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
  .stat-value { font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .stat-label { font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  section { margin: 2.5rem 0; }
  h2.section { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 1rem; padding-bottom: 0.4rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-strong); }
  h3.category { font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  #search { width: 100%; padding: 0.65rem 0.85rem; font-size: 0.95rem; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); border-radius: 6px; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; background: var(--surface); }
  #search:focus { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: 0; border-color: transparent; }

  .mermaid-wrap { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.5rem; overflow: auto; }
  .mermaid svg { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }

  .mental-model { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; }
  .mental-model h3 { margin: 1rem 0 0.4rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .mental-model h3:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .mental-model p { margin: 0 0 0.6rem; }
  .mental-model .flow { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 0.85rem; background: var(--surface-2); padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 4px; border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); margin: 0.4rem 0 0.8rem; }

  details.module { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0; overflow: hidden; }
  details.module summary { cursor: pointer; padding: 0.85rem 1rem; font-weight: 600; display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline; list-style: none; }
  details.module summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  details.module summary::before { content: "▶"; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--text-faint); transition: transform 0.15s; display: inline-block; }
  details.module[open] summary::before { transform: rotate(90deg); }
  details.module summary:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .mod-name { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; }
  .mod-desc { color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 400; flex: 1; }
  .mod-meta { display: flex; gap: 0.4rem; align-items: center; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-faint); }
  .gate-badge { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; background: var(--surface-2); padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--text-muted); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .tier-badge { padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.7rem; }
  .tier-independent { background: rgba(21,128,61,.1); color: var(--supported); }
  .tier-dependent { background: rgba(180,83,9,.1); color: var(--other); }
  .module-body { padding: 0.5rem 1rem 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .op { padding: 0.85rem 0; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border); }
  .op:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .op-header { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .op-id { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); }
  .op-summary { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem; }
  .transports { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.35rem; margin: 0.3rem 0; }
  .transport-pill { display: inline-flex; gap: 0.3rem; align-items: center; padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 999px; font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 0.72rem; background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .transport-pill .label { font-weight: 600; }
  .transport-pill[data-t="cli"] { border-color: var(--t-cli); color: var(--t-cli); }
  .transport-pill[data-t="rpc"] { border-color: var(--t-rpc); color: var(--t-rpc); }
  .transport-pill[data-t="call"] { border-color: var(--t-call); color: var(--t-call); }
  .transport-pill[data-t="expose"] { border-color: var(--t-expose); color: var(--t-expose); }
  .transport-pill[data-t="http"] { border-color: var(--t-http); color: var(--t-http); }
  .transport-pill[data-t="mcp"] { border-color: var(--t-mcp); color: var(--t-mcp); }
  .transport-pill[data-t="sdk"] { border-color: var(--t-sdk); color: var(--t-sdk); }
  .meta-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.9rem; margin-top: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .profiles { display: flex; gap: 0.25rem; }
  .profile-badge { padding: 0.05rem 0.45rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .profile-supported { background: rgba(21,128,61,.12); color: var(--supported); }
  .profile-unavailable { background: rgba(156,163,175,.2); color: var(--unavailable); text-decoration: line-through; }
  .profile-other { background: rgba(180,83,9,.12); color: var(--other); }
  .todo { color: var(--todo); font-style: italic; }
  .hidden { display: none !important; }
  a { color: var(--accent); }
  code { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 0.85em; }
  .empty-list { color: var(--text-faint); font-style: italic; padding: 1rem; text-align: center; }

  /* Layer pills in the diagram legend */
  .legend { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.8rem; }
  .legend span { padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 4px; }
  .legend .l-transport { background: var(--layer-transport); }
  .legend .l-cross { background: var(--layer-cross); }
  .legend .l-brick { background: var(--layer-brick); }
  .legend .l-deployment { background: var(--layer-deployment); }
  .legend .l-nexus_fs { background: var(--layer-nexus_fs); }
  .legend .l-rust_kernel { background: var(--layer-rust_kernel); }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    aside { position: static; height: auto; border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    main { padding: 1.5rem 1rem; }
    .stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="layout">
  <aside>
    <p class="brand">Nexus Surface Map</p>
    <p class="brand-sub">High-level API/RPC architecture</p>

    <h2>Bricks ({{ brick_categories.values() | sum(start=[]) | length }})</h2>
    {% for category, mods in brick_categories.items() %}
    <h2 style="font-size:0.65rem; opacity:0.7; margin-top:0.6rem;">{{ category }}</h2>
    {% for m in mods %}
    <a href="#m-{{ m.id }}">{{ m.id }}<span class="count">{{ ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) | length }}</span></a>
    {% endfor %}
    {% endfor %}

    {% for layer_label, mods in other_layers.items() %}
    <h2>{{ layer_label }}</h2>
    {% for m in mods %}
    <a href="#m-{{ m.id }}">{{ m.id }}<span class="count">{{ ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) | length }}</span></a>
    {% endfor %}
    {% endfor %}
  </aside>

  <main>
    <h1>Nexus API/RPC Architecture Map</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A high-level view of every external surface exposed by Nexus, organized around its real layered architecture: Rust kernel &rarr; NexusFS wrapper &rarr; 28 plugin-style <strong>bricks</strong> &rarr; deployment topology (hub / federation / zone / daemon / raft) &rarr; cross-cutting auth/profiles &rarr; transports (CLI / HTTP / gRPC / MCP / SDK).</p>

    <div class="stats">
      <div class="stat"><div class="stat-value">6</div><div class="stat-label">layers</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="stat-value">{{ total_bricks }}</div><div class="stat-label">bricks</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="stat-value">{{ total_transports }}</div><div class="stat-label">transports</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="stat-value">{{ total_ops }}</div><div class="stat-label">operations</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="stat-value">{{ total_missing }}</div><div class="stat-label">missing</div></div>
    </div>

    <input id="search" placeholder="Search by op-id, brick, transport name, or summary..." />

    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;1 Mental model</h2>
      <div class="mental-model">
        <h3>Layered architecture</h3>
        <p>Nexus is organized as five stacked layers. Most user-visible behavior lives in <strong>bricks</strong> &mdash; small, isolated feature modules that share nothing with each other and are wired together at boot by the brick factory based on the active deployment profile.</p>
        <p class="flow">transports  &rarr;  cross-cutting (auth, profile gates)  &rarr;  bricks  &rarr;  NexusFS  &rarr;  Rust kernel</p>

        <h3>Request flow: <code>nexus fs read /path</code></h3>
        <p>CLI parses <code>fs read /path</code> and calls into either a local NexusFS instance (embedded profile) or a remote SDK client (sandbox/full profile). The remote path goes through the gRPC <code>NexusVFSService.Call</code> with <code>method="sys_read"</code>; the server checks the syscall is in <code>KERNEL_SYSCALL_NAMES</code>, dispatches to <code>NexusFS.read()</code>, which descends through the mixin stack and into the Rust kernel to fetch bytes from the mounted backend. Brick hooks (e.g. <code>filesystem</code> for path scoping, <code>access_manifest</code> for fast-path ACL checks) can intercept the request before it hits the kernel.</p>

        <h3>Request flow: <code>nexus rebac grant alice read /path</code></h3>
        <p>Same transport, but <code>rebac_write</code> is <em>not</em> a kernel syscall. The gRPC dispatcher routes it to the brick layer&rsquo;s <code>ReBACManager.rebac_write()</code> through the legacy method-dispatch path. Auth middleware extracted the caller&rsquo;s identity from the JWT and populated <code>OperationContext</code>; the brick uses that context to enforce policy on the write itself.</p>

        <h3>Where ops live</h3>
        <p><strong>Kernel-native</strong> ops (sys_read, sys_write, sys_stat, &hellip;) execute in the Rust kernel via a thin Python wrapper. <strong>Brick-native</strong> ops (rebac_write, pay_debit, search_query, sandbox_execute, &hellip;) live entirely in Python under the respective brick. Both are exposed through the same transport surface so callers don&rsquo;t need to know which is which.</p>

        <h3>Profile gating</h3>
        <p>Each brick carries a <code>brick_gate</code> (e.g. <code>BRICK_REBAC</code>, <code>BRICK_PAY</code>) checked at boot. The <code>embedded &sub; lite &sub; sandbox &sub; full &sube; cloud</code> profile hierarchy controls which bricks are enabled. Surfaces exposed by a disabled brick fail with a stable error code so callers can detect the unsupported case.</p>

        <h3>Deployment topology</h3>
        <p>Beyond features, Nexus has a deployment dimension: <strong>zones</strong> are multi-tenancy units, a <strong>hub</strong> is an instance other nodes connect to, <strong>federation</strong> moves data and permissions between zones, the <strong>daemon</strong> hosts the runtime as a long-running process, and <strong>raft</strong> provides consensus for HA clusters. These cross-cut the bricks above and are visible as a separate layer in the architecture diagram.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;2 Architecture diagram</h2>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap">
        <div class="mermaid">
{{ mermaid_graph | safe }}
        </div>
        <div class="legend">
          <span class="l-transport">Transports</span>
          <span class="l-cross">Cross-cutting</span>
          <span class="l-brick">Bricks (28)</span>
          <span class="l-deployment">Deployment topology</span>
          <span class="l-nexus_fs">NexusFS</span>
          <span class="l-rust_kernel">Rust kernel</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;3 Bricks by category</h2>
      {% for category, mods in brick_categories.items() %}
      <h3 class="category">{{ category }}</h3>
      {% for m in mods %}
      <details id="m-{{ m.id }}" class="module" {% if loop.first and loop.index0 == 0 %}open{% endif %}>
        <summary>
          <span class="mod-name">{{ m.id }}</span>
          <span class="mod-desc">&mdash; {{ m.description }}</span>
          <span class="mod-meta">
            {% if m.brick_gate %}<span class="gate-badge">{{ m.brick_gate }}</span>{% endif %}
            {% if m.tier %}<span class="tier-badge tier-{{ m.tier }}">{{ m.tier }}</span>{% endif %}
            <span>{{ ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) | length }} ops</span>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="module-body">
          {% set ops = ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) %}
          {% if ops %}
          {% for op in ops %}
          {% include "_op_row.html.j2" %}
          {% endfor %}
          {% else %}
          <div class="empty-list">No external operations classified to this brick yet.</div>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
      </details>
      {% endfor %}
      {% endfor %}
    </section>

    {% if other_layers %}
    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;4 Other layers</h2>
      {% for layer_label, mods in other_layers.items() %}
      <h3 class="category">{{ layer_label }}</h3>
      {% for m in mods %}
      <details id="m-{{ m.id }}" class="module">
        <summary>
          <span class="mod-name">{{ m.id }}</span>
          <span class="mod-desc">&mdash; {{ m.description }}</span>
          <span class="mod-meta">
            <span>{{ ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) | length }} ops</span>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="module-body">
          {% set ops = ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) %}
          {% if ops %}
          {% for op in ops %}
          {% include "_op_row.html.j2" %}
          {% endfor %}
          {% else %}
          <div class="empty-list">No operations classified here yet.</div>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
      </details>
      {% endfor %}
      {% endfor %}
    </section>
    {% endif %}

    {% if orphan_modules %}
    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;4b Unclassified surfaces</h2>
      <p>Operations the classifier couldn't place. Add a rule in <code>scripts/surface_coverage/taxonomy.py</code> to route them.</p>
      {% for m in orphan_modules %}
      <details id="m-{{ m.id }}" class="module">
        <summary>
          <span class="mod-name">{{ m.id }}</span>
          <span class="mod-desc">&mdash; {{ m.description }}</span>
          <span class="mod-meta">
            <span>{{ ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) | length }} ops</span>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="module-body">
          {% for op in ops_by_module.get(m.id, []) %}
          {% include "_op_row.html.j2" %}
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </details>
      {% endfor %}
    </section>
    {% endif %}

    {% if missing_by_module %}
    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;5 Wanted but missing ({{ total_missing }})</h2>
      <p>Capabilities the architecture suggests should exist but currently don't. Subissues should open gap issues for each and link via the row's <code>gap_issue</code> field.</p>
      {% for module_id, ops in missing_by_module.items() %}
      <details class="module">
        <summary>
          <span class="mod-name">{{ module_id }}</span>
          <span class="mod-desc">&mdash; {{ ops | length }} missing surface(s)</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="module-body">
          {% for op in ops %}
          <div class="op">
            <div class="op-header">
              <span class="op-id">{{ op.id }}</span>
              <span class="op-summary">&mdash; {{ op.summary }}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-row">
              <span class="profiles">
                <span class="profile-badge profile-other">lite: missing_needed</span>
                <span class="profile-badge profile-other">sandbox: missing_needed</span>
                <span class="profile-badge profile-other">full: missing_needed</span>
              </span>
              {% if op.usage_example %}<span><em>{{ op.usage_example }}</em></span>{% endif %}
              <span>gap: {% if op.gap_issue %}<a href="https://github.com/nexi-lab/nexus/issues/{{ op.gap_issue }}">#{{ op.gap_issue }}</a>{% else %}<span class="todo">open one</span>{% endif %}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </details>
      {% endfor %}
    </section>
    {% endif %}

    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;6 Coverage status</h2>
      <p>This map is auto-extracted from source. Some transports are still partial:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>HTTP routes</strong>: scanned recursively under <code>src/nexus/server/api/</code>. Most product routes captured.</li>
        <li><strong>gRPC typed</strong>: only <code>vfs.proto</code> (NexusVFSService) &mdash; additional proto files not yet scanned.</li>
        <li><strong>SDK</strong>: walked <code>src/nexus/remote/</code> for any <code>*Client</code>/<code>*Backend</code>/<code>*Metastore</code>/<code>*Proxy</code> class. May miss helper modules.</li>
        <li><strong>MCP</strong>: from <code>tool_profiles.yaml</code>. Brick-level MCP registrations may add more at runtime.</li>
        <li><strong>FUSE</strong>: counted as a transport but has no @rpc_expose surface &mdash; the binary IS the surface.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section">&sect;7 Filling this map</h2>
      <p>Each op row has TODO slots that subissues fill: <em>usage example, correctness test, performance class, owner</em>. See <a href="api-rpc-surface-contract.md">api-rpc-surface-contract.md</a> for the contract.</p>
      <p>Profile epics fill rows in their slice: <a href="https://github.com/nexi-lab/nexus/issues/4119">#4119 lite</a> &middot; <a href="https://github.com/nexi-lab/nexus/issues/4120">#4120 sandbox</a> &middot; <a href="https://github.com/nexi-lab/nexus/issues/4121">#4121 full</a> &middot; <a href="https://github.com/nexi-lab/nexus/issues/4139">#4139 coverage matrix</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>
</div>

{{ mermaid_js | safe }}
<script>
mermaid.initialize({ startOnLoad: true, theme: 'default', securityLevel: 'loose', flowchart: { curve: 'basis', rankSpacing: 60, nodeSpacing: 30 } });

const search = document.getElementById('search');
search.addEventListener('input', () => {
  const q = search.value.trim().toLowerCase();
  document.querySelectorAll('.op').forEach(el => {
    const text = (el.dataset.opText || el.textContent).toLowerCase();
    el.classList.toggle('hidden', q.length > 0 && !text.includes(q));
  });
  document.querySelectorAll('details.module').forEach(d => {
    const ops = d.querySelectorAll('.op');
    if (ops.length === 0) return;
    const anyVisible = Array.from(ops).some(op => !op.classList.contains('hidden'));
    if (q.length > 0) { d.open = anyVisible; d.classList.toggle('hidden', !anyVisible); }
    else { d.classList.remove('hidden'); }
  });
});
</script>
</body>
</html>
